==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Naphthene
<hw>Naph"thene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A peculiar hydrocarbon fraction occurring as an ingredient of some
crude petroleums, mostly mixtures of derivatives of the five- and
six-membered saturated cyclic alkanes, cyclopentane and cyclohexane,
having the general formula C<sub>n</sub>H<sub>2n</sub>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naphthide</ent>⟦br⟧
